3. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - Although the paper does not explicitly mention computer vision, the robot's perception of its environment using sonar sensors can be considered a form of computer vision. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a machine learning algorithm for the robot to learn and detect deviations from its model of the environment. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - Although the paper does not explicitly mention neural networks or evolutionary computing, these concepts are commonly used in robotics and AI, and may be relevant to the algorithm proposed in the paper.
